# CEO (Build) Review - Pathwaize Intelligence Center

Verified the real build, not the report. Served `public/` and drove the demo headless (Chromium, no WebGPU adapter -> mock mode, which is the intended fallback).

## What I confirmed working (live)
- **Loads clean:** HTTP 200, `title=Pathwaize Intelligence Center`, zero pageerrors, zero console errors on first paint (only the expected "No available adapters" WebGPU warning under headless). All 12 JS files pass `node --check`; all ESM imports resolve.
- **Core workflow end-to-end (the brief's whole point):** prompt chip prefills input (106 chars) + switches tab -> Run Authority -> output card renders with `NEEDS REVIEW` status -> queue count = 1 -> Approve -> status advances and Push enables.
- **Approval gating enforced (critical requirement):** before approval `Push to LinkedIn` is `disabled:true`; only after Approve does it become `disabled:false`. No code path bypasses it. This directly answers the posting's "prevent approval-gated actions from publishing without approval."
- **Newsletter engine:** runs, produces output (1482 chars); schema + mock both carry `subject_lines[3]` + `preview_text` (posting explicitly asks for subject line options + preview text).
- **Revision workflow:** Request Edits opens the revision modal (visible, notes textarea present); revision creates a new output record rather than overwriting.
- **Knowledge Engine Lite:** category + Google Drive/GitHub destination controls present.
- **Intel Brief stub:** all 6 required sections present (What changed / working / leaking / needs action / Recommended decisions / Priority).
- **Run records + usage/cost + status tracking:** run log strip and stat panel increment (`Runs: 1`).
- **No em/en dashes** anywhere in the demo dir. Registry id 20 with verified tags.

## Feature richness vs target (10/10)
Meets it. Three real multi-step engines (route -> generate -> validate), backend-routed LLM contract (`LLMRouter.run()` provider-agnostic), WebLLM WebGPU with dual-model VRAM logic + graceful canned fallback, IndexedDB persistence (runs/outputs/logs/workspace), reflection retry, structured-output schemas, prompt chips, persistent intel input, workspace/subaccount indicator, output queue, intel brief. Implements the WebGPU agentic best-practices from the brief (prompt chaining over free ReAct, structured outputs, intent routing, 1-retry reflection). Bespoke dark execution-console design, not the portfolio look.

## Minor notes (non-blocking, for deploy-test to watch, no rebuild)
- All live verification ran in mock mode (headless has no WebGPU). Real WebLLM/Qwen path is unverified here; the 0.2.84-pin-then-latest-fallback catch covers it and mock keeps the flow fully demoable. deploy-test on real Chrome with WebGPU should confirm the actual model loads (risk already flagged by builder).
- `screenshot: null` — media-capture will supply the card hero later.

No fixes required. No earlier step needs redoing.

